references: The dataset is based on CDC Birth Cohort Linked Birth â€“ Infant Death Data Files

. It describes pregnancy and birth variables for all live births in the U.S. together with an indication of an infantâ€™s death before the first birthday. We used the data for 2015 (latest available), which includes information about 3,988,733 live births in the US during 2015 calendar year. The variables include demographic information about parents (age, ethnicity, education), birth order for the current child, pregnancy care and complications, delivery route, gestational age at birth, birth weight, apgar score, newborn care, etc. The dataset is widely used for risk profile analysis for specific causes of death (e.g., SIDS), as well as other undesirable outcomes, such as low birth weight and prematurity.
